<h1>Problem 1377 - 2022 Iran MO 3rd round C3 of 3, CG</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>We have \(n\ge3\) points on the plane such that no three are collinear. Prove that it's possible to name them \(P_1,P_2,\ldots,P_n\) such that for all \(1 < i < n\), the angle \(\angle P_{i-1}P_iP_{i+1}\) is acute.</p>
